sentences: Sixtoo was the main project of a Canadian underground hip hop DJ, producer and rapper Vaughn Robert Squire between 1996 and 2007.
Sixtoo rose to prominence in the mid 1990s underground hip hop scene initially as half of Halifax, Nova Scotia hip hop duo Sebutones, along with Buck 65.
In 2000, Sixtoo moved to Montreal where he signed on with UK based record label Vertical Form.
His debut album on the label, Chewing on Glass & Other Miracle Cures, has won acclaim in the international electronic beats community in 2004.
Sixtoo entirely produced Isaiah Toothtaker's Sea Punk Funk in 2012.
